Story time… 
Growing up, I had a few pieces of jewelry that I wore all the time— I mean ALL of the time. I never took off my small gold hoops, my bracelet with my name engraved on it, or my chain. Not only because we grew up in humble circumstances, but also because I have sensitive skin. Long story short, I really had no options. Fast forward twenty-something years later and I was able to invest in some pieces I really loved and was gifted some as well. 
For some reason, I could hardly justify buying it for myself. So, in the midst of my doctoral program (losing my mind and needing a hobby), I decided to make jewelry. I bought all of the necessary materials and tools and started making necklaces. 
Fast forward from there, I luckily had the support and love from my friends and family to start my own brand. I chose to stop pursuing my doctorate and focus on RMTL full-time. Here we are now— 15k customers later. 😉
Anything else you want to know? Let me know in the comments. 💘
